1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,680
I'll take my leave, so you can rest.

2
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:34,880
PREVIOUS EPISODE

3
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,080
I'll go with you.

4
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:40,480
Do you think this place is safe enough?

5
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,600
It's safe for now,

6
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:46,200
but I'll find a new place
for you to hide soon.

7
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:49,800
Thank you.

8
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:53,040
So this is Puna,
the girl who sang "Soft Heart"?

9
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:55,520
-I'm his ex.
-Yeah.

10
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:59,920
I can come and go as I please.

11
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,200
But you…

12
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:06,840
If we show the tape to the media,

13
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,680
we can prove we were framed.

14
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:12,480
I had the lawyer check.

15
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,200
There's still two weeks left.

16
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,680
Will that be enough time?

17
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:19,480
Yes. If we get it today, we'll make it.

18
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:22,520
Something's wrong with my phone.
The screen won't turn on.

19
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:27,680
-Where are they?
-At the phone shop over there.

20
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:29,680
Good. Lead the way.

21
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,160
Yes.

22
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,600
-Mom.
-Huh?

23
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:41,280
-They're here!
-Who, dear?

24
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:43,520
The ones I told you about.

25
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:47,600
Take your father out the back!
I'll close the door. Go!

26
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:01,680
Huh?

27
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:03,360
The shop was open just a moment ago.

28
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:07,400
Then check the back.

29
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:11,280
SCREEN PROTECTOR, FROM 100 BAHT

30
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,560
Open up!

31
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,959
I said open the door!

32
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:23,320
What are you staring at?

33
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:27,640
None of your business.
You'd better get going now!

34
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:35,840
Open the door!

35
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,640
It's here.

36
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:32,880
Hey, what are you doing?!

37
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:02,800
Wilai.

38
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:06,920
Don't stay in the house! Get out, quick!

39
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,920
The situation isn't safe.

40
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:24,320
Puna, who's that?

41
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:25,600
Oh!

42
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:30,040
This is Au. He's my friend.

43
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:33,400
Yes, my name is Au.

44
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:36,880
Once we have the tape,
should we copy it and give it

45
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:38,040
to every news outlet?

46
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:40,880
Calm down. Don't give the game away.

47
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:45,920
We need to send this tape
to headquarters first as evidence

48
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,720
to hold Singha and his gang accountable.

49
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:53,960
But we have to do it quietly,
or they'll catch on.

50
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:59,200
I agree. Those guys are sneaky.

51
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:02,600
If they find out in advance,
they might find a way to counter us.

52
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:06,200
You're right. I didn't think of that.

53
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,520
-Hey!
-Manat!

54
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:15,720
Where's the tape? Let me see it.

55
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:18,760
Just a sec.

56
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:32,920
Hey! Where's the tape?

57
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,760
It's gone. I don't know where it went.

58
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:45,800
Look properly!
How could it just disappear?

59
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:48,960
Come here. I'll help you look.

60
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:54,480
Whoa.

61
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,800
I must have dropped it somewhere.

62
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:08,080
Where though? Think carefully.

63
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:43,039
-Did you find it?
-Not at all.

64
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:44,840
Manat.

65
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:47,600
Are you sure
it could have fallen around here?

66
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:49,360
I parked the car right here.

67
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:51,960
If it fell, it should be nearby.

68
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,520
Excuse me.

69
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,640
We've driven all over

70
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:59,000
and have people searching.
Legs are sore, still nothing.

71
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,720
Manat.

72
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:04,240
Think carefully.
Did you stop anywhere else?

73
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,560
Maybe it fell there.

74
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,880
SCREEN PROTECTOR, FROM 100 BAHT
QUICK REPAIRS

75
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:18,320
KWANJAI MOBILE

76
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,520
Yes?

77
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,560
Isn't anyone at this shop?

78
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:24,240
Are you with the same people from earlier?

79
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,560
Which people?

80
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:29,000
Earlier, some thugs came,
but Kwan ran off before they got here.

81
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,040
Where did she go?

82
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:33,240
I don't know. Didn't get a chance to ask.

83
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:35,320
Do you have her number?

84
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,640
No, I don't have it.

85
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:39,480
She's quite guarded.
Doesn't want anyone hitting on her.

86
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,240
She doesn't give it out.

87
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:44,160
Please, don't ask me.
I don't want any trouble.

88
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:52,080
KWANJAI MOBILE

89
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:01,400
Her phone's off.
How am I supposed to reach Maria?

90
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:04,640
How's it going, Manat? Did you find it?

91
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,880
They probably came here,

92
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:09,240
but Maria got away in time.

93
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:11,040
Where did she go?

94
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,440
I don't know right now.

95
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:16,840
It's in this shop for sure, right?

96
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:20,360
It should be. I only stopped here.

97
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,800
And if it's not…

98
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:28,880
Calm down, Puna.

99
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:31,880
Whatever happens, we'll get the tape back.

100
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,160
I believe

101
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,240
we'll get the tape back.

102
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,720
Don't worry.

103
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:04,720
<i>Darling, listen to me</i>
<i>I have something to say</i>

104
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:09,800
<i>Pay close attention</i>
<i>Hear every word I give</i>

105
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,480
<i>The love</i>

106
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:14,800
-Boss.
-<i>I offer you</i>

107
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:18,880
<i>I willingly dedicate</i>

108
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:23,800
<i>To you, my lady</i>

109
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:29,920
Chart said you wanted to talk to me?

110
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,160
Yeah.

111
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:34,400
About the "My Request" sales contract.

112
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:37,960
Oh, right. I bought this song
for Sonrak to sing.

113
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:39,880
In a few days,
he can record it in the studio.

114
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:44,360
And the person who sold you the song…

115
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:47,080
That's Teacher Mueangphrai. Why?

116
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:52,720
Have you ever noticed
what this teacher's last name is?

117
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:56,800
Check the contract.

118
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:59,360
COPYRIGHT REGISTRATION
MR. MUEANGPHRAI DANWILAI

119
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:04,880
Danwilai. Sounds familiar.

120
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:06,160
Do you remember

121
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:09,080
Onanong Wongwichian?

122
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:11,920
What was her name before she went

123
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:14,520
into the industry?

124
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:18,840
Onanong Danwilai.

125
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:25,160
Same surname as Onanong.

126
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:28,280
Yeah.

127
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:33,080
Boss.

128
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:35,320
Why didn't you knock first?

129
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:38,920
Sorry, it's urgent.

130
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:44,040
My men, who were watching Tharin,
sent me this image.

131
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,160
What image?

132
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:58,880
Hey! What image?

133
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,120
Onanong!

134
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,360
Isn't it?

135
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:07,640
Yes.

136
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:11,200
It really is Onanong.

137
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:12,120
Hey…

138
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:13,920
She's still alive?

139
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:17,440
Yes. But that day,

140
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,760
I watched the car engulfed in flames.

141
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,280
Hard to believe she survived.

142
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:29,680
If this is Onanong,

143
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:33,320
then that means

144
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:37,360
that twin must be…

145
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,680
Phupha!

146
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:45,000
Yes.

147
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:51,160
I had someone watching him
because I believed

148
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:53,800
they must have swapped.

149
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:59,960
He's been deceiving us this whole time.

150
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:07,360
There's more.

151
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:12,360
My men also recorded audio
of the two of them talking.

152
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:14,480
Have a listen.

153
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:20,000
<i>What is it? Why did you want to meet me?</i>
<i>We could've just talked on the phone.</i>

154
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:22,360
<i>Coming out like this</i>
<i>could be trouble if we're seen.</i>

155
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:25,960
<i>Sorry. I'm just excited.</i>

156
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:27,360
<i>Excited? About what?</i>

157
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:29,360
<i>Puna just called.</i>

158
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:33,840
<i>She got the evidence tape</i>
<i>to use against Kitti and Singha.</i>

159
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:37,040
<i>Puna got the tape from the teddy bear?</i>

160
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:39,680
<i>Yes.</i>

161
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:43,240
<i>It's time we get back at them.</i>

162
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,960
<i>If we show the tape to the media,</i>

163
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:49,520
<i>we can prove we were framed.</i>

164
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:54,040
<i>But too bad, the case might be expired.</i>

165
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:55,040
<i>Not yet.</i>

166
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:58,440
<i>I had the lawyer check.</i>

167
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:03,000
-<i>There's still two weeks left.</i>
-<i>Two weeks?</i>

168
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:05,840
-<i>Will that be enough time?</i>
-<i>Yes.</i>

169
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:08,320
<i>If we get it today, we'll make it.</i>

170
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:11,960
<i>Finally, karma is catching up to them.</i>

171
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:14,080
<i>We have to thank Puna.</i>

172
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,440
<i>She made this possible.</i>

173
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:18,840
<i>Yes, Puna really deserves the credit.</i>

174
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,880
Is there anything I can help with?

175
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,640
I was going to send this one
to be cleaned too.

176
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,440
I can take it to wash.

177
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,880
Let it go! Give it to me!

178
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:38,720
-Give it to me!
-No!

179
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,560
Who took my teddy bear out?

180
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:47,280
That's why

181
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:50,960
Puna joined our company.

182
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:54,560
She was after the tape
hidden in this teddy bear!

183
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:15,880
There was a tape hidden in this.

184
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:19,400
And I never knew! Damn it!

185
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:26,280
So what does Puna have to do with this?

186
00:16:28,920 --> 00:16:30,280
Because Puna

187
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:33,680
is Phupha's daughter.

188
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:40,560
I just checked her records in HR.

189
00:16:41,680 --> 00:16:44,280
She really is Phupha's daughter.

190
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:49,360
We never even suspected it,
not for a second.

191
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,600
What's on that tape?

192
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:53,960
Why do they want it so badly?

193
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:58,120
<i>About what we were talking about just now,</i>

194
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:01,120
<i>I'm sure Phupha heard us.</i>

195
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:03,520
He must know we're dealing drugs.

196
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:05,280
<i>Hey!</i>

197
00:17:06,079 --> 00:17:07,960
<i>We can't let him live, Kitti.</i>

198
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:10,720
<i>Relax. I'll take care of it myself.</i>

199
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,079
<i>How are you going to handle it?</i>

200
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,440
-<i>With this gun.</i>
-<i>If that's the case,</i>

201
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:18,280
<i>don't let it lead back to us.</i>

202
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,720
<i>How about this?</i>

203
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:23,960
Have Chart go to his house

204
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:27,040
and make it look like an accident.
Sound good?

205
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:31,520
Yeah. As for you, go see Kamnan.

206
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:33,600
Make sure he smooths things over
with the drugs.

207
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:39,240
I'll go find Chart
and tell him to deal with Phupha.

208
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:41,800
Okay.

209
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:47,440
Phupha.

210
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,320
You're dead.

211
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,360
Maria.

212
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:05,520
You've seen it, right?

213
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,600
Where did you get that tape?

214
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:09,640
I think Manat dropped it earlier today.

215
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,600
This is serious.

216
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:14,480
What should we do, Dad?

217
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:17,760
If they know we have the tape,

218
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:19,360
they'll kill us for sure.

219
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:22,720
Don't tell anyone.

220
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:31,560
Before we ordered them killed that day,

221
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:35,960
Phupha overheard us
talking about delivering the drugs.

222
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:49,080
So we sent Chart to kill him,
and suddenly, Onanong appeared.

223
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:53,040
She showed up to arrange
a birthday surprise for Kamnan.

224
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:01,520
Have Chart go to his house

225
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:04,000
and make it look like an accident.

226
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:05,840
-Sound good?
-Yeah.

227
00:19:06,480 --> 00:19:08,280
Hey! What's going on?

228
00:19:09,960 --> 00:19:12,480
Did Onanong secretly set up a camera?

229
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:13,600
Huh?

230
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:17,400
Then she heard and saw everything we said?

231
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:20,840
Chart!

232
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:23,760
Bring them here and get that tape for me!

233
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:26,000
Yes, Boss.

234
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:41,800
Wong, split up
and search the place thoroughly.

235
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:43,560
-Go.
-Yes, Chart.

236
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:48,600
And you, follow me.

237
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:09,920
Search everywhere.

238
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:22,760
-Hey.
-Chart,

239
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:26,240
no one's here. I've checked every room.

240
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:30,200
That means Onanong
might have realized it first.

241
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:34,120
But if we track Puna,

242
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:37,560
I think we might find Onanong.

243
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:39,040
Yeah, good.

244
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:43,280
Then let's go find Puna. Go.

245
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:45,640
Yes.

246
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:52,480
Dad, should I give the tape to the police?

247
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:57,080
Would that be a good idea?

248
00:20:58,040 --> 00:21:00,640
If they get arrested, it'll be over.

249
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:02,840
We won't have to keep hiding like this.

250
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:06,560
I don't think it'll end, dear.

251
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:09,200
Most of the police are on their side.

252
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:12,600
If anything goes wrong,
we might be the first ones they go after.

253
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:15,080
You're right.

254
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:19,360
Then should I give the tape to Manat?

255
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:24,120
But I don't remember his number.
I don't know how to contact him.

256
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,440
Don't contact anyone for now.

257
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:29,000
Just keep quiet.

258
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:31,600
Don't meet anyone. It's dangerous.

259
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:33,720
Okay, Dad.

260
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:38,760
Where should we hide the tape?

261
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:41,000
Just hide it for now. Don't tell anyone.

262
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:43,920
Don't even tell your mom.

263
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,040
Okay.

264
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:52,080
BAI TONG MUSIC

265
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:04,120
Let's stay at the company tonight.
No need to go see Wilai.

266
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:09,600
If we go and there's no tape,
Aunt Wilai will be disappointed.

267
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:13,080
I'm sorry for what Manat caused,

268
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,200
for all this trouble.

269
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:16,560
Never mind.

270
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:20,560
Nobody intended for this to happen.

271
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:27,160
I promise I'll get the tape back.

272
00:23:32,080 --> 00:23:35,680
Oh, Puna, Teacher!
Where have you two been?

273
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:38,240
I'm sorry, Emily.

274
00:23:38,320 --> 00:23:42,240
We had urgent business,
so we didn't contact you.

275
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:43,880
Come on, let's sit down first.

276
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:54,920
Do you have something you want to discuss?

277
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:58,320
Puna is really trending right now.

278
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:00,080
"Soft Heart" is doing very well,

279
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:03,000
and "My Request" is also strong.

280
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:06,240
Both songs are hot at the same time.
It's the song you composed, right?

281
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,040
Yes.

282
00:24:08,120 --> 00:24:10,040
The boss listened

283
00:24:10,120 --> 00:24:12,480
and really liked it. He wants to buy it.

284
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:14,280
Well…

285
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:17,000
You're all here?

286
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:19,920
Sonrak is livestreaming right now.

287
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:21,720
Look.

288
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:28,400
<i>Don't let anyone hug these shoulders</i>

289
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:34,120
<i>Don't let anyone grab these hands</i>

290
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:39,600
<i>Don't let anyone kiss this forehead</i>

291
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:45,160
<i>Don't let anyone caress these cheeks</i>

292
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:49,240
How did that sound?
For today, I'll just sing this much.

293
00:24:49,320 --> 00:24:52,240
I'll make the MV
for everyone to watch later.

294
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:54,560
That's it for today,
ending the livestream here.

295
00:25:01,640 --> 00:25:04,200
When Sonrak said that, what did he mean?

296
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:07,080
It's your song. You composed it.

297
00:25:07,160 --> 00:25:10,640
And he's singing it. How is that allowed?

298
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:12,280
Exactly.

299
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,760
Or maybe…

300
00:25:14,840 --> 00:25:18,560
I already sold this song
to Darathong Music.

301
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:20,320
Why didn't you tell me?

302
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:25,400
Exactly. You're with our company, right?

303
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:28,840
If you were selling it,
it should've been to us.

304
00:25:31,080 --> 00:25:34,240
I have to apologize to everyone
on behalf of Teacher Mueangphrai.

305
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:36,080
It really was necessary.

306
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:39,040
The two of us
didn't want to do this at all.

307
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:42,880
Yes. But if the boss finds out,

308
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:44,320
he'll probably be very disappointed.

309
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:59,720
Dam, someone from Darathong Music
is outside the company.

310
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:21,760
Is that someone from Darathong?

311
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:28,920
Yes, those are the people
Singha keeps around.

312
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:31,800
What are they doing here?

313
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:35,920
They seem suspicious.

314
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:38,280
Puna.

315
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:42,120
You shouldn't go anywhere right now.
It's dangerous.

316
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:46,040
Okay, I won't go anywhere.

317
00:26:48,520 --> 00:26:51,360
Puna, I think they already know.

318
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:02,160
Chart ordered us to hunt down Puna.

319
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:06,080
-Where do we start looking?
-Wherever you find her, handle it there.

320
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:07,240
Yeah, let's go.

321
00:27:20,360 --> 00:27:22,400
Who are you planning to catch, young man?

322
00:27:24,280 --> 00:27:26,480
Who we catch is none of your business.

323
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:28,440
It definitely has to do with me.

324
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:40,160
You bastard!

325
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:56,720
DARATHONG MUSIC

326
00:27:57,920 --> 00:28:00,240
What about Onanong? Where did she go?

327
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:04,200
I checked her house,

328
00:28:04,280 --> 00:28:07,600
but she probably knew and escaped in time.

329
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:11,080
Did she go hide with Phupha?

330
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:13,960
I didn't see her at Phupha's house either.

331
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:18,160
I've assigned my men to watch.

332
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:21,320
Do you want me to capture her now?

333
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:23,440
No.

334
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:28,960
If we act now, they might ambush us.

335
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:32,000
Better to wait until we're sure.

336
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:33,400
Yes.

337
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:35,400
I have my men

338
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:38,480
watching Puna and Mueangphrai.

339
00:28:38,560 --> 00:28:42,200
I'll report immediately
if there's any movement.

340
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:57,240
The shop's still not open.

341
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:02,480
It's past opening time,
probably won't open.

342
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:06,280
Do you know if Kwanta has another house?

343
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:10,280
She has a house near Dong Maprao,
but I don't know which one.

344
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:14,360
Let's go check it out.

345
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:17,840
-Thank you very much.
-Yes.

346
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:20,120
Let's go.

347
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:25,480
Boss.

348
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:28,120
My man, Hoi, reported

349
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,560
seeing Chaiya and Manat

350
00:29:30,640 --> 00:29:34,120
hanging around near the phone repair shop.

351
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:37,080
Why were they there?

352
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:39,720
My men reported seeing them yesterday,

353
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:43,280
and today they came back again.

354
00:29:43,360 --> 00:29:45,560
I think those two

355
00:29:46,600 --> 00:29:47,960
seem suspicious.

356
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:49,600
Send someone to their house.

357
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:53,520
Check it carefully.
Make sure who they really are.

358
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:55,280
-Go.
-Yes, Boss.

359
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:07,000
His chest is broad,
his shoulders are broad.

360
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:11,760
Wow, look at that!

361
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:15,840
Nammon, you're here.
Come help me with the work, quick!

362
00:30:17,640 --> 00:30:20,920
Oh, I can't, Auntie.

363
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:23,360
Because I just got my nails done.

364
00:30:23,440 --> 00:30:26,880
If I help you now, my nails

365
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:30,040
won't be beautiful anymore.
They'll get all scratched and ruined.

366
00:30:30,120 --> 00:30:33,520
Geez, then why did you do them?
You can't do anything like this.

367
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:34,680
Just cut them short?

368
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:36,360
No, I can't!

369
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:38,000
Just so you know,

370
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:41,200
this is Chaiya's shirt, your ex.
Aren't you going to help?

371
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:46,840
No, I'm too lazy.

372
00:30:46,920 --> 00:30:48,640
Oh, but that's just how it is.

373
00:30:48,720 --> 00:30:52,800
Even if you ironed his shirt,
he wouldn't get back together with you.

374
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:55,480
Do you know why? Because right now,

375
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:57,560
he has someone in his heart.

376
00:30:58,320 --> 00:30:59,960
Yes, that's me.

377
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:05,560
Feels good to iron
the shirt of my future husband.

378
00:31:06,240 --> 00:31:09,080
Look at his arms, muscular and strong!

379
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:13,280
Keep going, Auntie! Keep going!

380
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:16,120
You don't need to cheer me on.
I don't need encouragement.

381
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:18,960
Just being able to do something
for the man I love,

382
00:31:19,040 --> 00:31:22,200
that's enough to fill me with motivation.

383
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:26,160
-Auntie.
-What now?

384
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:28,320
I'm curious about something.

385
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:30,920
There's a room with no one in it.

386
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:33,960
That's Chaiya's storage room.

387
00:31:34,600 --> 00:31:37,480
What's inside?
Why is it locked so securely?

388
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:39,600
The lock is so strong!

389
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:42,480
You're too curious!

390
00:31:42,560 --> 00:31:44,880
How should I know? I'm not his wife yet.

391
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:48,760
Wait until I am,
then I'll tell you everything.

392
00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:52,200
Men really like keeping secrets, huh?

393
00:31:52,280 --> 00:31:54,000
Ugh, they love to gossip.

394
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:59,320
-Auntie.
-Huh?

395
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:04,400
-Why can't you ask for it in Thai?
-Do you have them?

396
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:06,400
If I'm not smart,
I wouldn't know what it means.

397
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:09,520
The keys, here they are.

398
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:14,360
I have them, but I won't give them to you.

399
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:19,960
I'll keep them and wear them on my wrist.

400
00:32:22,080 --> 00:32:23,000
Like a bracelet.

401
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:34,680
Uncle, do you know
where Kwanta's house is?

402
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:36,880
No, I don't.

403
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:39,280
Do you know Village Head Prueng?

404
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:41,880
He runs a coffee shop
at Nern Samran village.

405
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:43,320
Never seen him.

406
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:46,960
Try asking Dong Maprao's village head.
His house is that way.

407
00:32:47,040 --> 00:32:48,920
-Thanks a lot, Uncle.
-Sure.

408
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:49,840
Let's go.

409
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:17,040
These perverts are loaded with stuff.

410
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:23,520
-Chaiya, Manat.
-Hey.

411
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:25,840
-Someone's here. Go hide!
-Are you there? I've brought laundry!

412
00:33:30,680 --> 00:33:33,440
Alright, I'm coming in.

413
00:33:33,520 --> 00:33:36,040
Wait a minute! Whoa.

414
00:33:36,120 --> 00:33:39,680
Very rude and self-centered.

415
00:33:39,760 --> 00:33:41,000
Who are you talking about?

416
00:33:42,280 --> 00:33:45,800
I'm not talking about anyone
in particular, not Auntie either.

417
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:49,160
I'm just talking
about people who act rudely

418
00:33:49,240 --> 00:33:52,920
and enter someone else's house
without the owner's permission.

419
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:55,160
-I'm the owner of the house!
-Oh.

420
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:58,680
Stop talking. Let's go in, quickly!

421
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:00,800
Let's get in.

422
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:02,960
Oh, wait.

423
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:04,480
-The door isn't locked.
-Huh?

424
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:07,760
I wonder if anyone's undressed?

425
00:34:07,840 --> 00:34:10,679
Oh! Wait, Auntie.

426
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:14,000
If someone's undressed like that,
we have to…

427
00:34:14,679 --> 00:34:17,560
-We… Go in! Or we'll miss it.
-What?

428
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:19,560
Hold on! Miss what?

429
00:34:19,639 --> 00:34:23,159
That's my boyfriend! Chaiya!

430
00:34:29,679 --> 00:34:31,520
Oh no!

431
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:33,920
Why is the doorknob like this?

432
00:34:35,920 --> 00:34:38,800
-What room is this?
-Their storage room.

433
00:34:40,800 --> 00:34:42,480
I'm curious.

434
00:34:42,560 --> 00:34:45,000
What do guys keep in their storage room?

435
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:47,600
Nammon!

436
00:34:54,080 --> 00:34:55,360
I can't take this!

437
00:34:55,440 --> 00:34:57,080
So shocking!

438
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,840
Oh my goodness!

439
00:35:03,800 --> 00:35:06,200
Seeing this, my heart

440
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:08,200
is racing!

441
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:13,000
Even this room's full of stuff like this.

442
00:35:13,080 --> 00:35:16,760
The secret room must have more!

443
00:35:18,080 --> 00:35:20,920
This must be that Au guy's doing!

444
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:24,360
If this secret room belongs to Au,

445
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:27,760
the extra room they rented
must belong to Chaiya and Manat.

446
00:35:27,840 --> 00:35:29,240
Oh.

447
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:30,680
Secret room?

448
00:35:32,080 --> 00:35:33,680
Oh, Nammon!

449
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:37,360
Then you have to check it out
and prove it!

450
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:40,160
Nammon, what are you doing?

451
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:44,000
Auntie, let her go! Nammon, open the room!

452
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:48,400
Auntie, don't stop her!

453
00:35:54,680 --> 00:35:55,960
Follow them!

454
00:35:58,600 --> 00:36:00,840
The village head doesn't know
where Kwanta's house is.

455
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:02,920
Where are we supposed to look?

456
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:05,280
I think we should go back
and talk at home.

457
00:36:12,320 --> 00:36:14,440
I only want Chaiya dead!

458
00:36:14,520 --> 00:36:15,800
The others don't matter!

459
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:33,800
Who do you think hired these two?

460
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:38,080
Right now, there's only one person
who hates me. Sonrak.

461
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:48,600
Why are you taking the keys?
Give them back! Oh no!

462
00:36:49,760 --> 00:36:52,440
Nammon! Give them here!

463
00:36:52,520 --> 00:36:55,120
-Auntie, listen to me.
-Let go!

464
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:59,360
Let the young ones handle this.
Elders stay out of it!

465
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:02,160
Ugh, you guys really get along!

466
00:37:02,240 --> 00:37:04,480
I'm slapping you first!

467
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:06,360
What elders? Nammon, stop!

468
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:09,800
Just open it!

469
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:13,560
Auntie, I just want to see what's inside.

470
00:37:13,640 --> 00:37:15,160
-No! You can't!
-Hey.

471
00:37:15,240 --> 00:37:16,440
Wait.

472
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:19,280
I told you, no! Let go!

473
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,760
Quick!

474
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:21,960
-Stop!
-Hey!

475
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:24,640
Who are you guys?

476
00:37:28,560 --> 00:37:30,040
-Come here, quick!
-Wait!

477
00:37:30,120 --> 00:37:31,480
-Hold on!
-Don't shoot!

478
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:34,560
Don't tell me you're going

479
00:37:34,640 --> 00:37:35,920
to sexually assault me!

480
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:38,400
Shut up!

481
00:37:40,040 --> 00:37:41,120
Hey! Watch them!

482
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:05,240
POL. CAPT. CHAIYA DEVAPITHAK
POL. LT. MANAT ASWASUKPHONG

483
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:06,760
They're cops!

484
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:17,680
Chit, Chaiya and Manat are cops!

485
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,760
What? Cops?

486
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:26,960
Hey, don't run!

487
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:30,120
Stop right there!

488
00:38:30,200 --> 00:38:32,480
Anybody, help!

489
00:38:32,560 --> 00:38:34,320
If anyone hears me, help!

490
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:36,680
Chaiya!

491
00:38:36,760 --> 00:38:38,800
Help me, please!

492
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:42,080
-They're going to hurt us! Help, please!
-That's right!

493
00:38:42,160 --> 00:38:48,440
Please help me!
They're planning and trying to assault me!

494
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:54,320
So everyone's here! Chaiya! Manat!

495
00:38:57,000 --> 00:38:59,680
Ugh, old lady!
Why are you blocking the way?

496
00:38:59,760 --> 00:39:00,760
Old lady? Who's old?

497
00:39:02,760 --> 00:39:04,160
Who are you talking about?

498
00:39:04,240 --> 00:39:05,320
All of you, get out!

499
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:06,640
Split up!

500
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:08,080
Get out of the way!

501
00:39:23,720 --> 00:39:25,880
Chaiya, you're dead.

502
00:39:28,720 --> 00:39:31,200
-Oh no! Hey!
-More!

503
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:33,480
Good job!

504
00:39:33,560 --> 00:39:36,480
-Oh, Auntie!
-No! I didn't do it!

505
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:37,760
She did it!

506
00:39:42,520 --> 00:39:45,720
A gun! Why did I grab this? No, I didn't!
She grabbed it!

507
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:49,040
Yes, I grabbed it just a moment ago.

508
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:52,400
Are you crazy, Auntie? This is a gun!

509
00:39:52,480 --> 00:39:53,880
Throw it! Let it go!

510
00:39:56,200 --> 00:39:59,320
I'm sorry!
I didn't mean it. It was a mistake.

511
00:39:59,400 --> 00:40:00,880
Please don't hurt me!

512
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:14,800
I'm sorry too!
Please don't assault me, Mr. Thief.

513
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:17,840
-I know my body might tempt you, but…
-Stop!

514
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:20,640
No one said they're going to assault you!

515
00:40:20,720 --> 00:40:23,000
His gaze is obvious.

516
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:24,480
Everyone!

517
00:40:24,560 --> 00:40:28,560
I've called police, water, fire,
electricity, rescue team, everyone!

518
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:30,800
You're doomed! Leave now!

519
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:32,680
-Just go!
-Hold on.

520
00:40:32,760 --> 00:40:34,280
Why call the electricity company?

521
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:35,920
The water department too! What for?

522
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,280
Auntie! To help us, of course!

523
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:38,680
-Hey! Stop!
-How can electricity help?

524
00:40:38,760 --> 00:40:40,200
This is the police!

525
00:40:40,280 --> 00:40:42,720
We've got you surrounded. Surrender now!

526
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:45,720
The police are here! We did it!

527
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:47,240
-The police are here!
-Help me, please!

528
00:40:52,640 --> 00:40:55,520
-Wong, move! The police are here!
-Help me! We're here!

529
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:57,440
-Help me, please!
-This way!

530
00:40:57,520 --> 00:40:59,160
Hurry up, Officer!

531
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:04,400
Everyone, ready? Who did I come with?
Wait, I came alone!

532
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:14,160
Charan, the cops are here! Hurry!

533
00:41:14,240 --> 00:41:15,640
Quick, get out of here!

534
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:24,520
Captain, they've all run away.

535
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:30,280
Thanks so much, Au.
Without you, we'd have had a hard time.

536
00:41:31,240 --> 00:41:32,720
No problem.

537
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:35,040
Chaiya!

538
00:41:35,120 --> 00:41:39,680
Hey, you knew I was here, right?
That's why you came to help. Oh, Manat!

539
00:41:39,760 --> 00:41:42,600
Thank you. You're the sweetest!

540
00:41:42,680 --> 00:41:43,920
-Oops.
-What?

541
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:45,880
No one got hurt, right?

542
00:41:46,880 --> 00:41:49,960
You're a police officer.
Why didn't you tell me?

543
00:41:50,040 --> 00:41:52,680
Do you know how close Auntie was

544
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:54,920
to dying?

545
00:41:56,920 --> 00:41:59,800
-I almost got assaulted too.
-Huh?

546
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:02,400
But thankfully…

547
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:04,240
-I'm still safe.
-Gives me chills.

548
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:05,440
I've never been touched

549
00:42:05,520 --> 00:42:07,800
-Alright.
-by any man.

550
00:42:07,880 --> 00:42:09,760
Hey! Can you stop imagining things?

551
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:11,080
Who's going to assault you?

552
00:42:12,040 --> 00:42:14,680
-I'm not imagining!
-Yeah.

553
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:16,560
-Because I know…
-What?

554
00:42:16,640 --> 00:42:18,200
my curvy body

555
00:42:18,280 --> 00:42:20,600
-is sexy, naughty,
-All out!

556
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:23,280
-and sassy.
-Yeah.

557
00:42:23,360 --> 00:42:26,680
-The thief likes it! Right?
-Yeah.

558
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:31,120
-Dada. If it were between you
-Yes?

559
00:42:31,200 --> 00:42:33,000
and the snake slithering into my house…

560
00:42:33,080 --> 00:42:35,120
-You'd smack the snake, right?
-I'd smack you!

561
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:38,840
Smack me once and then cuddle?

562
00:42:38,920 --> 00:42:40,080
I'd even kick you!

563
00:42:40,160 --> 00:42:41,560
Kicking the bike to buy flowers?

564
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:43,040
Yeah, but they're corpse flowers!

565
00:42:43,120 --> 00:42:45,320
-Whoa, a corpse flower like this!
-Yeah.

566
00:42:45,400 --> 00:42:46,840
It's deadly enough to drive you away!

567
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:50,720
I love it! I love a guy
who's a little violent.

568
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:53,120
Ugh, what am I gonna do with you?

569
00:42:53,200 --> 00:42:55,240
Hey! Stop it!

570
00:42:56,880 --> 00:42:57,800
Chaiya!

571
00:42:58,400 --> 00:43:00,920
You're really a cop, right?

572
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:04,160
Huh?

573
00:43:06,560 --> 00:43:08,000
This is true, right?

574
00:43:12,760 --> 00:43:13,880
-Tell me.
-Ugh.

575
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:19,200
If these three know,
tomorrow everyone will!

576
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:20,480
Right?

577
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:25,280
I'm really pissed!
I never thought those two were cops!

578
00:43:25,360 --> 00:43:28,160
Yes, sir. Thank you very much.

579
00:43:28,240 --> 00:43:30,120
Yes, goodbye.

580
00:43:32,840 --> 00:43:34,000
Who are you calling?

581
00:43:34,680 --> 00:43:37,800
Deputy Chief Phuchong.
He's not answering, probably in a meeting.

582
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:40,480
So what do we do now?

583
00:43:42,920 --> 00:43:44,320
Everything in the car?

584
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:45,680
Last load, Captain.

585
00:43:46,560 --> 00:43:49,960
Let's find a hiding spot,
then we figure out the next move.

586
00:43:53,600 --> 00:43:56,920
Kitti, tell me. Can we still fix this?

587
00:43:57,000 --> 00:44:01,360
Yes. The higher-ups promised
to back us fully.

588
00:44:01,440 --> 00:44:05,440
But they have proof
that we were the ones dealing the drugs!

589
00:44:05,520 --> 00:44:07,480
It's fake!

590
00:44:08,960 --> 00:44:10,600
They told me to play it this way.

591
00:44:11,480 --> 00:44:12,920
What do we do?

592
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:15,480
Here's the plan. They said

593
00:44:16,480 --> 00:44:20,680
to make Chaiya and Manat
look like the drug dealers.

594
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:23,680
It has nothing to do with us.
And the evidence they got,

595
00:44:24,360 --> 00:44:27,120
it is fake and made

596
00:44:27,760 --> 00:44:29,360
to frame us

597
00:44:30,640 --> 00:44:32,040
and blackmail us.

598
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:38,080
Okay. We all need to stick to the story.

599
00:44:39,160 --> 00:44:41,280
We're the victims!

600
00:45:02,160 --> 00:45:03,640
Who are you calling?

601
00:45:04,560 --> 00:45:07,920
I called Aunt Wilai, but her phone's off.

602
00:45:09,600 --> 00:45:11,320
I tried calling her too, but no answer.

603
00:45:12,280 --> 00:45:14,280
Try calling Uncle Tharin.

604
00:45:16,400 --> 00:45:17,240
Okay.

605
00:45:25,720 --> 00:45:27,760
He's not answering either.

606
00:45:27,840 --> 00:45:29,280
I'm starting to get worried.

607
00:45:32,680 --> 00:45:34,480
Should we go check at the house, Teacher?

608
00:45:34,560 --> 00:45:36,680
What about the guy guarding the office?

609
00:45:56,120 --> 00:45:57,480
Dam! Den!

610
00:45:57,560 --> 00:45:59,480
What are you peeking at?

611
00:45:59,560 --> 00:46:00,920
Yeah.

612
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:02,920
We're checking on those guys
from yesterday.

613
00:46:03,520 --> 00:46:05,280
See if they're still around.

614
00:46:05,360 --> 00:46:07,040
They left yesterday.

615
00:46:07,640 --> 00:46:08,920
But…

616
00:46:09,480 --> 00:46:11,240
my heart

617
00:46:11,800 --> 00:46:15,920
hasn't moved on.
It's still with you, Puna.

618
00:46:18,440 --> 00:46:22,600
My heart's still here too,
always free for you, Puna.

619
00:46:25,400 --> 00:46:26,920
Beauty gets to choose.

620
00:46:27,640 --> 00:46:31,440
Let's go, Puna.
Just let them keep dreaming.

621
00:46:32,680 --> 00:46:34,080
Keep dreaming?

622
00:46:36,400 --> 00:46:39,600
-They really left already, Teacher.
-Then let's go too.

623
00:46:39,680 --> 00:46:41,240
Puna, where are you going?

624
00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:44,600
-I have some errands. Please step aside.
-I'll give you a ride.

625
00:46:44,680 --> 00:46:47,320
No, I'm going with Teacher Mueangphrai.

626
00:46:47,920 --> 00:46:49,560
Are you still mad at me?

627
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:52,840
What am I supposed to do
to make you forgive me?

628
00:46:53,840 --> 00:46:55,120
Mr. Sonrak.

629
00:46:57,400 --> 00:46:58,560
There's no chance anymore.

630
00:46:59,360 --> 00:47:03,640
I appreciate your feelings,
but I need to be honest.

631
00:47:04,400 --> 00:47:07,720
There's no way this can work between us.

632
00:47:09,720 --> 00:47:11,600
-Excuse me.
-Puna.

633
00:47:11,680 --> 00:47:14,520
Puna, listen to me! Puna!

634
00:47:30,240 --> 00:47:31,120
Get out!

635
00:47:32,640 --> 00:47:33,920
I said get out!

636
00:47:38,560 --> 00:47:39,680
You aren't done yet, huh?

637
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:42,840
As long as you're alive,
the game isn't over.

638
00:47:45,520 --> 00:47:46,880
Then bring it on.

639
00:48:12,160 --> 00:48:14,040
-Teacher, that's Chaiya!
-Whoa!

640
00:48:14,760 --> 00:48:17,040
This is bad! I'll call the police.

641
00:48:21,640 --> 00:48:22,680
Chaiya!

642
00:48:25,280 --> 00:48:26,880
Puna, don't go! It's dangerous!

643
00:48:26,960 --> 00:48:29,720
You guys deserve to die like stray dogs.

644
00:48:30,560 --> 00:48:31,640
-Let go!
-Whoa!

645
00:48:32,400 --> 00:48:34,640
-Chaiya!
-Puna!

646
00:48:59,600 --> 00:49:00,800
This is for you!

647
00:49:06,920 --> 00:49:09,920
My whole life is for you, my girl.

648
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:12,000
Why are you standing here, Wilai?

649
00:49:12,080 --> 00:49:15,360
I've never done anything wrong,
never had an evil thought.

650
00:49:15,440 --> 00:49:16,480
NEXT EPISODE

651
00:49:16,560 --> 00:49:19,520
Namthip, Onanong.

652
00:49:19,600 --> 00:49:21,840
Do you have a video player?

653
00:49:21,920 --> 00:49:23,640
I want to see her when she was alive.

654
00:49:25,240 --> 00:49:26,880
I miss Mom.

655
00:49:26,960 --> 00:49:28,640
Send word to Puna.

656
00:49:28,720 --> 00:49:31,200
If it's not necessary,
don't come back to this house

657
00:52:29,040 --> 00:52:32,760
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
